# ERP DMS — AI-First Upload-to-Fill Standard

**Standard document:** `docs/standards/ERP_DMS_AI_FIRST_UPLOAD_TO_FILL_WORKFLOW_STANDARD.md`  
**Investigation report:** `implementation_Review/ERP_DMS_10A_AI_FIRST_UPLOAD_TO_FILL_WORKFLOW_INVESTIGATION_AND_REDESIGN_REPORT.md`  

---

## Core Rule

> The primary DMS document creation path is: **Upload → AI Fills → User Reviews → Approve & Save.**  
> Manual field entry before upload is a FALLBACK, not the default.

---

## Required Flow for File-Based Document Creation (DMS.11 — Option A Implemented)

```
1. User uploads file → dms-temp bucket (upload session created)
2. User clicks "Upload & AI Fill" → startAiIntakeFromUploadSession(uploadSessionId)
3. System downloads temp file, extracts PDF text or base64-encodes images
4. AI provider classifies + extracts all fields
5. Result stored in dms_ai_extraction_results with upload_session_id (no document yet)
6. dms_upload_sessions.intake_status → "review_pending"
7. Redirect to /dms/intake/[sessionCode]
8. User reviews AI-filled form (editable, confidence badges shown)
9. User clicks "Approve & Save" → approveAiIntakeAndCreateDocument()
10. Final dms_documents record created, file copied dms-temp → dms-documents
11. Version v1 + file record created, metadata/tags/links/expiry reminders saved
12. dms_upload_sessions.intake_status → "approved", document_id set
13. Redirect to final document at /dms/documents/record/[documentId]
```

---

## Prohibited Patterns — Hard Violations

```
❌ Auto-save AI suggestions to dms_documents or dms_document_metadata_values without user action
❌ Require title or document_type_id BEFORE AI runs in the AI-first intake path
❌ Show AI results only in a separate tab (not in the creation/review form)
❌ Allow AI to change document type / category without user review
❌ Log OCR text, AI prompt content, or raw AI responses
❌ Return API keys to the client
❌ Populate dms_document_metadata_values before applyAiResultToDocument() is called
```

---

## Required Server Actions

| Action | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `createDraftDocumentFromUpload(uploadSessionId)` | Minimal draft, status=pending_ai_review, copies file |
| `runDmsAiAnalysisForDocument(documentId)` | Existing DMS.10 action — call automatically after draft creation |
| `applyAiResultToDocument(documentId, aiResultId, accepted, metadataValues)` | Confirm-save: writes accepted values, sets status=active, writes audit |

---

## Required DB State

- `dms_upload_sessions.document_id` — FK to dms_documents after intake draft created
- `dms_documents.status = "pending_ai_review"` — valid status for AI intake drafts
- `dms_ai_extraction_results.ai_status` — must be set to "accepted" on approval

---

## AI Review Screen Requirements

Every AI review screen MUST:
- Show AI-suggested values as **pre-filled editable controls** (not static text in a tab)
- Show a **confidence badge** (high/medium/low/needs_manual_review) per field
- Validate required fields (title, type, category) before allowing Approve & Save
- Have footer buttons: `Approve & Save` | `Save Draft` | `Re-run AI` | `Discard`
- Never auto-submit

---

## Status Values

- `draft` — manual creation, no AI
- `pending_ai_review` — AI intake in progress, awaiting user review
- `pending_review` — awaiting human approvals workflow
- `active` — finalized after review
- Other statuses unchanged from DMS.2

---

## UX Copy

| Context | Label |
|---|---|
| Main intake button | "Upload & AI Fill" |
| Review approval | "Approve & Save" |
| Review save without finalize | "Save Draft" |
| Re-trigger AI | "Re-run AI" |
| Cancel intake | "Discard" |
| Old manual path | "Create Manually" |

